I noticed the Atari cases on that site. I had previously followed the
thread on an Atari forum.

The peroxide attacks and removes the discolored surface layer, which
removes the glossy surface and leaves the plastic porous. Their
suggestion to top off with a clear coat can alleviate that. I don't
know that the result would be acceptable on vinyl.

John

